#Text=Do you feel that there should have been more of a fine line drawn between the money you received , between  prize " and " work , " for tax purposes ?

column1: #Text=AM : Yes !
#Text=The money was at one point on the show classified as a prize and we never even thought about taxes .
#Text=This would make the prize more inconsiderable if it was called " $ 65,000 total prize winnings " to all the viewers .
#Text=MH : You discuss many horrible housing situations during your reign as Top Model .
#Text=Were you not allowed to make your own decisions as far as housing was concerned ?
#Text=AM : In the beginning , no .
#Text=My parents and I were told where I would stay , and what I could and mostly could not bring .
#Text=The second housing was because I refused to live in the first dwelling and again this was an arranged accommodation .

#Text=After seeing how nasty this second place was ( mice in my bed ) , I decided to make a decision and see what I could afford in terms of rent close to what I was already paying ( $ 650 ) in another place in Toronto [ that was ] NOT in someone 's house .
#Text=This is where I found [ the final place ] , the only available place for this price ... a place on Parliament Street .
#Text=The nasty side of town .
#Text=Her brief modeling career
#Text=MH : Your spread in Fashion magazine only paid $ 500 .
#Text=Is that a competitive rate for models or do you feel that you were paid less because you were under your television contract ?
#Text=AM : That is incorrect ; I was paid zero dollars for the Fashion shoot .
#Text=I was paid $ 500 for a wedding magazine front page and spread .
#Text=This dollar amount is standard in the business for this job - apparently whether you are Canada 's Next Top Model or not .
#Text=MH : Why do you feel CityTV did not back you , as you say they were going to , during the lawsuit with your previous agency ?
#Text=AM : The truth ?
#Text=We never got them to sign on their promises to my parents and I. They knew this and we were naive and did n't .
#Text=Everything these days is officialized only if it is in writing .
#Text=So , they claim now that they never said such things and [ told us ] to deal with the situation as these things happen every day .
#Text=MH : The Canadian website
#Text=Canoe said you had alleged that Jeanne Beker , a judge on the show , effectively " ruined your career .
